<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF7FFD6A5CDFDAE1D57FC4D" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5CDFDAE1FEEFD51" blockId="7.[136,465,630,657]" box="[136,465,630,657]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFF7FFD6A5CDFDAE1FEEFD51" box="[136,465,630,657]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="4">
1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A5E1FDAF1EC5FD51" box="[164,250,630,657]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5E1FDAF1EC5FD51" bold="true" box="[164,250,630,657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aloysia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF7FFD6A444FDAE1F00FD51" box="[257,319,631,657]" name="Palau" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paláu</collectingCountry>
(1784: 767).
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5CDFD661D57FC4D" blockId="7.[136,1452,703,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Shrubs, monoecious, branches without prickles, aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences axillary, simple, racemes spiciform, multiflorous, rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, green; bracteoles absent. Flowers pedicellate; calyx tubular, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 4-lobed, accrescent in fruit; corolla sub-actinomorphic, 4-lobed; stamens 4, included to slightly exserted, didynamous, superior pair without connective appendages, tecae parallel; ovary 1-carpelate, 2-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma 2-lobed. Fruit a schizocarp, with 2 cluses, brown, external surface smooth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF7FFD6A5F8FC4E1D38FB49" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF7FFD6A5F8FC4E1D38FB49" blockId="7.[136,1452,703,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A5F8FC4E1F2EFC71" box="[189,273,919,945]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5F8FC4E1F2EFC71" box="[189,273,919,945]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aloysia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A485FC4E1D35FC71" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[448,778,919,945]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Lantaneae">
Lantaneae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A707FC4E1D3CFC71" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[578,771,919,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A7CDFC4E1CFEFC71" box="[648,705,919,945]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and currently presents 36 species of disjunct distribution in the temperate and subtropical regions of North and South America (O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A6ADFC621A1FFC15" box="[1000,1056,955,981]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A128FC621B7CFC14" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J." box="[1133,1347,954,981]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="193 - 212" refId="ref36202" refString="Moroni, P., O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J. (2016) Species delimitation in the Aloysia gratissima complex (Verbenaceae) following the phylogenetic species concept. Botanical journal of the Linnean Society 180: 193 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / boj. 12369" type="journal article" year="2016">
Moroni 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A18CFC621B3EFC15" box="[1225,1281,955,981]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A5CDFC061F10FC38" box="[136,303,991,1017]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). In North America, there are four species, and 32 are distributed through South America. Only 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF7FFD6A0D6FC061EC1FBDC" authorityName="Troncoso" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="Gillies &amp; Hooker ex Hooker" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gratissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A0D6FC061EC1FBDC" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. gratissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in both hemispheres (O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A796FBDA1D31FBDD" box="[723,782,1027,1053]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A625FBDA1A7FFBDD" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J." box="[864,1088,1026,1053]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="193 - 212" refId="ref36202" refString="Moroni, P., O'Leary, N. &amp; Filloy, J. (2016) Species delimitation in the Aloysia gratissima complex (Verbenaceae) following the phylogenetic species concept. Botanical journal of the Linnean Society 180: 193 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / boj. 12369" type="journal article" year="2016">
Moroni 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A6FBFBDA1DC6FBDD" box="[958,1017,1027,1053]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Considered monophyletic, the genus is characterized by the morphological synapomorphy of an evenly 4-lobed calyx (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A132FBFE1B51FB81" author="Lu-Irving, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; O'Brien, A. &amp; Olmstead, R. G." box="[1143,1390,1063,1089]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="644 - 655" refId="ref35306" refString="Lu-Irving, P., O'Leary, N., O'Brien, A. &amp; Olmstead, R. G. (2014) Resolving the genera Aloysia and Acantholippia within tribe Lantaneae (Verbenaceae), using chloroplast and nuclear sequences. Systematic Botany 39: 644 - 655. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364414 X 680816" type="journal article" year="2014">
Lu-Irving 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF7FFD6A1AAFBFE1B16FB81" box="[1263,1321,1063,1089]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Ten species are recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF7FFD6A4D8FB921FDBFBA5" box="[413,484,1099,1125]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, all of them occurring in the Atlantic Forest, of which six are endemic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF7FFD6A070FB921F07FB49" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref36092" refString="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. (2020 a) Aloysia in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15122 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Moroni &amp; O’Leary 2020a</bibRefCitation>
). There are two species in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFF7FFD6A725FBB61D3CFB49" box="[608,771,1135,1161]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
